<section ID="chapter.widgets.space">
  <TITLE>Tdspace and lrspace widgets</TITLE>
<subsection> <TITLE>Description</TITLE>

<P>
These widgets skip blank spaces. <<tdspace>> skips vertical space while <<lrspace>> skips horizontal space. They naturally only take one pixel of size in the opposite direction, so they are often glued to take all available space (<<tdspace(glue:we)>> and <<lrspace(glue:ns)>>.

<subsection> <TITLE>Parameters</TITLE>

<P>
<LIST>
&param_background;

<ITEM> <<width:I>> : Specifies the amount of vertical or horizontal space to skip. <<I>> must be a valid screen distance (see <ptr to="misc.distance">).

&param_glue;
&param_padx;
&param_pady;
&param_feature;
&param_handle;
&param_tooltips;

</LIST>

</P>

<subsection> <TITLE>Interface</TITLE>

<P>
The object you get by an handle on the widget implements the following methods :

<LIST>

&interface_set;
&interface_get;
&interface_bind;
&interface_getFocus;
&interface_setGrab;
&interface_releaseGrab;
&interface_getGrabStatus;
&interface_raise;
&interface_lower;
&interface_winfo;

</LIST>
</section>
